  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIf the validator experiences a hard reboot (power loss) when it comes back online it fails to start with the following error\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO Lighthouse started                      version: Lighthouse/v1.0.0-c6baa0ee\r\nINFO Configured for testnet                  name: pyrmont\r\nINFO Starting validator client               validator_dir: \"/var/lib/lighthouse/validators\", beacon_node: http://localhost:5052/\r\nINFO Completed validator discovery           new_validators: 0\r\nERRO Failed to initialize validator          validator: 0xb...., error: LockfileExists(\"/var/lib/lighthouse/validators/0xb..../keystore-m_12381_3600_1_0_0.json.lock\")\r\nCRIT Failed to start validator client        reason: Unable to initialize validators: LockfileExists(\"/var/lib/lighthouse/validators/0xb.../keystore-m_12381_3600_1_0_0.json.lock\")\r\nINFO Internal shutdown received              reason: Failed to start validator client\r\nINFO Shutting down..\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n1.0.0\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe application should be able to handle rebooting after a power loss. We could clean up the lock files automatically or find a way to handle them gracefully. \r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nDeleting the lock files manually fixes the issue but is annoying to have to do every time the machine has a power loss.\r\n",
